# Celeborn — the derived search index is regenerable; never commit it.
**/.context/index.db
**/.context/index.db-*

# This repo's OWN working memory is private. A public repo means a public
# .context/, so we do NOT ship our development journal/state. The format is
# demonstrated via examples/sample-.context/ instead. (Root-anchored so the
# example dir is unaffected.)
/.context/

# Secrets — Stripe keys, webhook secrets, etc. NEVER commit.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Per-project harness install dirs — regenerated by `celeborn grok sync-rules` / the adapter
# installers every session (managed blocks). The committed SOURCE adapters live in grok/ and codex/.
.grok/
.codex/

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
*.egg-info/
dist/
build/
packaging/.version

# Celeborn Automatic Context Record is LOCAL-ONLY (verbatim prompts + paths).
# It still rides `celeborn sync`.
.context/auto/
.context/activity.md

# Celeborn derived task board (regenerable from tasks.md)
.context/tasks.json

# Celeborn prompt outbox — local per-agent hand-off queues, drained into the live session.
.context/outbox/

# Celeborn board viewer runtime (ensure-on-orient) — local-only.
.context/.board.pid
.context/.board.log

# Celeborn integrity manifest — generated per release by `celeborn integrity --write` and bundled into
# the shipped package; never committed (so source/editable checkouts stay 'unverified' = no dev nag).
references/integrity.json

# GitHub App private keys — NEVER commit
*.pem
*private-key*

# npm workspace install (CELE-t98 / t112) — the root install hoists deps here; the per-app
# node_modules are ignored by board/.gitignore + web/.gitignore. The shared package is source-only
# and ships no node_modules of its own, but ignore it defensively.
/node_modules
/packages/*/node_modules

# Vercel link/credentials for the root-rooted hosted-board deploy (CELE-t113). The web/ deploy
# now runs `vercel` from the repo root (Root Directory=web set on the project), so the link dir
# lives here too. Same as web/.gitignore's `.vercel` rule — never commit it.
/.vercel
